2026-06-19T02:30:42.9095018Z Loading required package: DBI
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9095260Z > 
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9095450Z > # CRAN guard
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9095640Z > #
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9096058Z > # The duckdb test suite exercises DuckDB's bundled C++ engine, which is too heavy
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9096723Z > # for CRAN's check farm, and checks were very fragile in the past. We therefore
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9097328Z > # keep it off on CRAN but run it automatically on GitHub Actions (GITHUB_ACTIONS)
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9097908Z > # and on r-universe (MY_UNIVERSE). An explicit DUCKDB_R_RUN_TESTS opts in
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9098500Z > # (true-ish) or out (false-ish) and always wins; otherwise we fall back to those.
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9099512Z > # This check is intentionally inlined here (rather than calling into the package)
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9100524Z > # so the guard is obvious and self-contained.
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9101372Z > run_tests <- tolower(trimws(Sys.getenv("DUCKDB_R_RUN_TESTS", "")))
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9102029Z > 
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9102519Z > if (run_tests %in% c("true", "1", "yes", "on")) {
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9102863Z +   run <- TRUE
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9103468Z + } else if (run_tests %in% c("false", "0", "no", "off")) {
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9103965Z +   run <- FALSE
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9104179Z + } else {
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9104552Z +   run <- tolower(trimws(Sys.getenv("GITHUB_ACTIONS", ""))) == "true" ||
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9105089Z +     nzchar(trimws(Sys.getenv("MY_UNIVERSE", "")))
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9105610Z + }
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9105896Z > 
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9106449Z > if (run) {
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9106851Z +   test_check("duckdb")
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9107204Z + } else {
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9107408Z +   message(
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9107606Z +     "\n",
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9107991Z +     strrep("=", 78),
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9108232Z +     "\n",
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9108484Z +     "Skipping the duckdb test suite.\n",
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9108801Z +     "\n",
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9109529Z +     "The duckdb tests exercise DuckDB's bundled C++ engine and are deliberately\n",
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9110162Z +     "NOT run on CRAN. They run automatically on GitHub Actions (including\n",
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9110759Z +     "r-universe). This keeps check time and resource usage on CRAN within\n",
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9111373Z +     "acceptable limits and helps release duckdb in a predictable and controlled\n",
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9111805Z +     "manner.\n",
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9112027Z +     "\n",
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9112443Z +     "This is intentional, not an oversight. duckdb has an extensive test suite\n",
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9113104Z +     "that runs continuously in our own CI; see <https://github.com/duckdb/duckdb-r>.\n",
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9113546Z +     "\n",
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9113969Z +     "To run the test suite locally, set the environment variable before checking:\n",
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9114575Z +     "  Sys.setenv(DUCKDB_R_RUN_TESTS = \"true\")    # from within R, or\n",
2026-06-19T02:30:42.9115124Z +     "  DUCKDB_R_RUN_TESTS=true R CMD check ...      # from the shell\n",
